    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Director, FBI",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "Re: RECOVERY OF \"FLYING DISC\",",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "NORTH HOLLYWOOD, CALIFORNIA,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "JULY 9, 1947",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "July 17, 1947",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "On the following day, July 10, 1947, one [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "the North Hollywood, reported that on this morning he was at",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "the North Hollywood Service Station eating at which time there was",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "considerable talk about the flying disc having been found in the vicinity.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "A number of what appeared to be young high school students were present",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "and were having quite a laugh about the excitement caused by the finding",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "of the disc. [REDACTED] stated that he received a definite impression that",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "these young students either had themselves or knew of someone who had been",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "working for the past two weeks making this \"flying disc\". [REDACTED] was",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "unable to furnish the names of any of these young men but identified one",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "of them who was making the statements as being employed in a Chevron",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "Service Station at the corner of Victory Boulevard and Whitsett Street.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "He described the youngster as about sixteen years of age.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "The above information was also furnished to the G-2 Office at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
